#. TRANSLATOR: Label Trust classification for a candidate that cannot be
#. verified. "policy" here refers to SELinux/MLS security policy — do not
#. generalise to "politique" without the security context. Retain the
#. variant name prefix in English as it is a type identifier, not prose.
#: components/rusty-gadgets/umrs-uname/src/main.rs:1405
msgid "UntrustedLabelCandidate — do not use for policy"
msgstr ""

#. TRANSLATOR: A label whose structure is valid but whose integrity has not
#. been confirmed by independent evidence. "structurally valid" = well-formed;
#. "integrity unconfirmed" = no digest or ownership check passed yet.
#: components/rusty-gadgets/umrs-uname/src/main.rs:1409
msgid "LabelClaim — structurally valid; integrity unconfirmed"
msgstr ""

#. TRANSLATOR: Highest trust level. T4 = integrity anchored tier. "ownership"
#. = file ownership in the package database; "digest" = cryptographic hash.
#: components/rusty-gadgets/umrs-uname/src/main.rs:1413
msgid "TrustedLabel — T4: ownership + digest verified"
msgstr ""

#. TRANSLATOR: T4 integrity was verified BUT a contradiction was also found
#. between independent evidence sources. The label passed the crypto check
#. but the system state is internally inconsistent. Abbreviated to fit the
#. fixed column width — full detail is in the secondary row below.
#: components/rusty-gadgets/umrs-uname/src/main.rs:1422
msgid "Verified w/ Contradiction — T4 integrity + conflict"
